---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

// Placeholders replacing local assets
const bgImage1 = "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1544928147-79a2dbc1f389?q=80&w=2560&auto=format&fit=crop";
const bgImage5 = "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1582555172866-f73bb12a2ab3?q=80&w=1000&auto=format&fit=crop";
const bgImage3 = "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1566127444979-b3d2b654e3d7?q=80&w=1000&auto=format&fit=crop";
const bgImage6 = "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1572953109213-3be62398eb95?q=80&w=1000&auto=format&fit=crop";
---

<BaseLayout title="About Us | Museo Bulawan" theme="light" navTheme="light">
  
  <!-- Hero -->
  <div class="w-screen h-[40rem] bg-cover bg-center bg-no-repeat absolute top-0 left-0 -z-10" style={`background-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(255,255,255,0.2), rgba(255,255,255,1)), url('${bgImage1}')`}></div>

  <div class="w-full max-w-[140rem] mx-auto px-8 md:px-16 lg:px-32 pt-64 pb-24 flex flex-col gap-32 text-black">
    
    <!-- Part 1 -->
    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-16">
      <div class="md:w-2/5">
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-justify leading-relaxed text-gray-700">
          The Museo Bulawan, also known as the Community Museum of Camarines Norte, embodies the rich cultural and historical essence of the province. Its origins trace back to 1995, when the construction of a new neo-classical provincial capitol building provided a fitting backdrop for the establishment of a museum.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-8 w-full h-[400px] bg-cover bg-center rounded-lg shadow-xl" style={`background-image: url('${bgImage5}')`}></div>
      </div>
      <div class="md:w-3/5">
        <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-serif mb-10 text-[#DAB765] font-bold leading-tight">
          "A museum is a bridge that connects the past to the present, inspiring the future."
        </h1>
        <h2 class="font-serif font-semibold text-4xl mb-6">Humble Beginnings</h2>
        <div class="space-y-6 text-xl text-gray-700 text-justify leading-relaxed">
          <p>Initially, the museum was situated in a modest space at the center of the capitol building's frontage, directly facing the main entrance. Despite its limited size, this initial venue served as a hub for various periodic exhibits.</p>
          <p>Through collaborations with national organizations such as the National Commission for Culture and the Arts (NCCA), the National Museum, and the National Historical Institute, the museum hosted numerous events that sparked a growing interest in local history.</p>
          <p>These early efforts laid the groundwork for a vibrant cultural hub that would eventually grow into a larger and more comprehensive institution.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="w-full h-px bg-gray-300"></div>

    <!-- Part 2 -->
    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-16 items-center">
      <div class="md:w-1/2">
        <div class="w-full h-[500px] bg-cover bg-center rounded-lg shadow-xl" style={`background-image: url('${bgImage3}')`}></div>
      </div>
      <div class="md:w-1/2">
        <h2 class="font-serif font-bold mb-8 text-5xl">Expansion and Transformation</h2>
        <p class="text-2xl text-gray-700 text-justify leading-relaxed">
          The new location facilitated significant advancements in museum management, including systematic techniques in documentation, research, preservation, and exhibition. Enhanced marketing and promotional efforts further broadened the museum's reach.
        </p>
        <div class="flex mt-8 gap-6 items-start">
          <div class="text-[12rem] font-serif font-bold text-[#DAB765] leading-[0.75]">O</div>
          <p class="flex-1 text-xl text-gray-700 text-justify mt-4 leading-relaxed">
            ver time, the museum's popularity and collections grew, outstripping the capacity of its original location. The year 2000 marked a pivotal moment in its history when the museum was relocated to a larger building adjacent to the provincial capitol.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Part 3 -->
    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-16 bg-[#1C1B19] text-white p-12 lg:p-24 rounded-3xl shadow-2xl items-center">
      <div class="md:w-3/5">
        <h1 class="text-5xl font-serif font-bold mb-8 text-[#DAB765]">A Beacon of Cultural Wealth</h1>
        <p class="text-2xl leading-relaxed text-white/90">
          The museum's name, Museo Bulawan translated as "Golden Museum"—reflects Camarines Norte's distinction as a province historically linked to gold mining. This golden legacy resonates in the collections:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-8 space-y-4 text-xl text-white/80">
          <li><strong>Numismatics:</strong> An extensive collection of coins and currencies.</li>
          <li><strong>Portraits of Governors:</strong> A gallery honoring the province's leaders.</li>
          <li><strong>Historical Panels:</strong> Displays illustrating local and national history.</li>
          <li><strong>Local Heroes:</strong> Tributes to individuals who shaped the province.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="md:w-2/5 w-full h-[400px] bg-cover bg-center rounded-xl" style={`background-image: url('${bgImage6}')`}></div>
    </div>

    <!-- Vision & Mission -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-16">
      <div class="bg-gray-100 p-16 rounded-3xl text-center flex flex-col items-center justify-center border border-gray-200 shadow-lg">
        <h1 class="text-5xl font-serif font-bold mb-8 text-black">Our Vision</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          Museo Bulawan is the leading and the most viewer-friendly community museum that serves as the prime center for education and communication of the rich cultural, artistic, and natural heritage and history of Camarines Norte.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-gray-100 p-16 rounded-3xl text-center flex flex-col items-center justify-center border border-gray-200 shadow-lg">
        <h1 class="text-5xl font-serif font-bold mb-8 text-black">Our Mission</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          Collect, research, conserve, exhibit and disseminate knowledge of significant past to enhance social life. We educate, entertain, and excite through systematic preservation and publication of material culture.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>